- We can use following Automation tools to Build UI Applications.

1. bower

2. Gulp

3. Grunt

4. Karma

bower.
    - bower is the Automation tool Given By NodeJS.

    - bower used to download the required dependencies to develop UI Application.

bower installation.

>npm install -g bower

bower components
-
    - we have two bower components.

1.bower.json

2. .bowerrc


bower.json
-
    - used to mention the required resources to develop UI Application.

.bowerrc
-
    - used to indicate the path to the resources downloading by using bower.


bower.json
-
{
    "name":"nareshit",   // "developer name" / "project name"
    "dependencies":{     // required dependencies
        "angular":"~1.6.0",   // "~" used to download latest version.
        "bootstrap":"~3.3.6"
    }
}


/*
    JSON - JavaScript Object Notation

    Objects  -- { }

    Arrays   -- [ ]

    data    --  "key & value"

*/


.bowerrc
-
{
    "directory":"bower_components"
}


Executing the Bower Components
-
> bower install

-------------------
bowerdemo
    bower.json
    .bowerrc
    bower_components
        angular
           angular.min.js

        bootstrap
            dist
                css
                    bootstrap.min.css

                js
                    bootstrap.min.js

        jquery
              dist
                    jquery.min.js
    ----------------------------------

index.html
-
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    //Business Logic Here
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="bower_components/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <script src="bower_components/angular/angular.min.js"></script>
    <script src="bower_components/jquery/dist/jquery.min.js"></script>
</html>

uninstall the packages by using bower.
-
bower uninstall bootstrap

list of dependencies.
-
bower list


installation of dependencies dynamically.
-
bower install ngstorage --save

















































































